description: India's e-commerce scene is transforming.  Quick commerce and online retailers are merging services.  Established players like Flipkart and Amazon are exploring 10-minute deliveries.  Swiggy, Blinkit, and Zepto are expanding their product range. They now offer larger items like appliances.  Companies are increasing warehouse sizes to accommodate this shift.  This competition is changing how Indians shop.
title: 10-minute delivery bright spot for 'dark' stores
Many states not on board to lower insurance rate

description: Amidst a political clash concerning Ambedkar's legacy, the JD(U) countered AAP after Kejriwal suggested Nitish Kumar consider Amit Shah's remarks on the Dalit icon.  JD(U)'s Sanjay Jha highlighted Kumar's appointment of a Mahadalit CM, contrasting it with Kejriwal's actions. Jha also pointed to Shah's criticism of Congress's treatment of Ambedkar, emphasizing the NDA's inclusive approach towards a developed India.
title: ‘You neglected Dalits’: JDU slams Arvind Kejriwal, supports Amit Shah

description: A deadly collision between an LPG tanker and a truck on the Jaipur-Ajmer National Highway resulted in a series of explosions, claiming 12 lives and injuring at least 33. The inferno engulfed over 40 vehicles, including sleeper buses. Ten bus passengers and a former IAS officer are missing.
title: 12 die, 40 vehicles gutted as tanker crash triggers blasts on Jaipur-Ajmer highway

description: A joint parliamentary committee (JPC) of 39 members, chaired by P.P. Chaudhary, will scrutinize the 'one nation, one election' bills.  The committee, comprising members from various parties, including 22 from NDA and 15 from the opposition, will examine the proposed mechanism for simultaneous polls and submit its report by the next session's final week.
title: Mega panel of 39 MPs to take up one nation, one election bills

description: An Indian-American businessman, facing a hefty Rs 500 crore alimony payment to his first wife, has been ordered by the Supreme Court to pay Rs 12 crore to his second wife after a brief marriage. The court criticized the second wife's demand for alimony equal to the first wife's, emphasizing that alimony aims to prevent destitution, not equalize wealth.
title: Can't expect man to maintain ex-wife as per his status all his life: SC

description: Google has reportedly reduced its top management roles by 10% as part of an ongoing efficiency drive. CEO Sundar Pichai confirmed this in a recent all-hands meeting, stating the company has been simplifying its structure. This follows significant layoffs in 2023 and a warning of further job cuts in 2024.
title: Pichai to employees: Google layoffs cut 10% of managers, directors, VPs

description: A car plowed into a crowded Christmas market in Magdeburg, Germany, leaving at least one dead and up to 80 injured. The driver has been arrested, and authorities are investigating the incident. Chancellor Olaf Scholz expressed condolences, while regional officials described the event as "terrible.
title: Tragedy at German Christmas market as speeding car leaves one dead, dozens injured

description: Parliament's winter session concluded amidst unprecedented chaos, marked by low productivity, protests, and even physical altercations.  The session saw minimal legislative output, with only one bill passed.  While debates on the Constitution's 75th anniversary offered a moment of reflection, the Speaker issued a stern warning against disruptive behavior as the session ended abruptly.
title: Chaotic winter session ends: LS worked for 57% of the time, RS for 43%

description: A Jaipur mechanic, Radheyshyam Choudhary, became a victim of a horrific gas tanker explosion.  Engulfed in flames, he stumbled 600 meters, crying for help while bystanders filmed.  Despite recounting the ordeal to his brother, he succumbed to 85% burns at SMS Hospital.
title: Rajasthan tragedy: Man in flames walked 600m seeking help, but people just recorded videos

description: A devotee in Thiruporur accidentally dropped his iPhone into a temple's donation box. The temple authorities refused to return it, stating anything dropped in the hundi becomes temple property.  They offered him the SIM card and access to the data, but the devotee pleaded for the phone's return, leaving its fate in the temple's hands.
title: Phone dropped in hundi by accident, temple claims it in Tamil Nadu

description: Karnataka High Court ordered the immediate release of BJP MLC CT Ravi on Friday. Police arrested him on Thursday for allegedly making derogatory remarks against state minister Laxmi Hebbalkar. Ravi alleged mistreatment and a head injury caused by police, accusing Deputy CM DK Shivakumar and Hebbalkar of orchestrating an attack.
title: Arrest rules not followed, set BJP MLC CT Ravi free: HC

description: Lucha Libre pioneer Rey Misterio Sr., uncle and trainer of WWE Hall of Famer Rey Mysterio, passed away at 66.  Misterio Sr. wrestled for decades, last competing in 2023.  He significantly influenced professional wrestling, mentoring his nephew and other luchadores. AAA and the wrestling community mourn his loss, celebrating his enduring legacy.
title: RIP Rey Mysterio Sr.: Lucha Libre Royalty Dies at 66

description: States pitched for special central packages during pre-budget consultations.  They sought increased interest-free loans, disaster relief funds, and infrastructure support. Kerala requested a substantial package citing fiscal stress, while Punjab asked for an industrial package similar to J&K's.  Several states also requested increased honorarium for ASHA workers.
title: Punjab, Kerala seek special financial package

description: Trinamool Congress MP Derek O'Brien criticized Rajya Sabha Chairman Jagdeep Dhankhar for allegedly speaking for nearly 30% of the Upper House's functional time during the winter session. O'Brien questioned if this constituted a new parliamentary record. This follows an unsuccessful attempt by opposition members to remove Dhankhar, citing bias and lack of trust.
title: Dhankhar spoke for ‘30%’ of RS time in Parliament winter session: TMC

description: A dispute over incense in a Kalyan building escalated into a Marathi vs. non-Marathi conflict, leading to the arrest of MTDC officer Akhilesh Shukla and two others for assaulting their Marathi neighbors.  The incident sparked outrage in the Maharashtra assembly, with CM Fadnavis assuring strict action. Shukla denies making anti-Marathi remarks, claiming it was a personal dispute.
title: Marathi vs non-Marathi fight flares up in Maharashtra over lighting of incense
Time to end infiltration via borders of 2 ‘friendly neighbours’: Shah in WB
HC dismisses petition against award of Dharavi project to Adani

description: Taylor Swift's new album, 'The Tortured Poets Department,' features songs referencing her relationship with Travis Kelce.  Lyrics in songs like 'The Alchemy' and 'So High School' allude to football, Kelce's attempts to connect with her, and their budding romance.  Even a lyric change in 'Karma' during a concert highlighted Kelce's presence, confirming Swift's new love interest.
title: All the Taylor Swift songs which hint at a Travis Kelce reference

description: A fatal highway accident near Jaipur involving an LPG tanker and a truck highlighted the lack of cloverleaves at the NH48-Ring Road junction.  Unfinished four years after the road's inauguration, these missing exits force dangerous U-turns at Bhankrota and Mahapura, causing frequent accidents. Land acquisition issues and contractor problems have delayed the cloverleaf construction until March 2026.
title: Rajasthan tragedy could have been averted had planned cloverleaves come up

description: Indian chess prodigy Arjun Erigaisi urgently appeals for his passport's return after visa processing delays. He needs it to travel to New York City for the World Rapid & Blitz Championships, starting December 26th. The prestigious tournament boasts a $1.5 million prize pool and a revamped format, attracting top players like Magnus Carlsen and Hikaru Nakamura.
title: India's no.1 chess player faces US visa trouble

description: The Indian National Developmental Inclusive Alliance (INDIA) bloc experienced internal friction during the winter session of Parliament, with regional parties challenging the Congress's leadership.  Disagreements arose on issues like the Adani controversy and EVM usage.  However, Amit Shah's Ambedkar remarks united the opposition in protest, offering a temporary reprieve for the Congress amidst its electoral struggles and alliance tensions.
title: Double trouble: How Congress navigated winter storm in Parliament

description: Prithvi Shaw, the 25-year-old Mumbai batter, is facing criticism over his fitness, discipline, and attitude. A Mumbai Cricket Association official revealed that even senior players have complained about Shaw's behavior. Shaw responded to the criticism with a cryptic social media post, hinting at unfair judgment.
title: 'Don't speak...': Shaw shares cryptic post after MCA's criticism

description: Alabama became the 20th US state to incorporate Sikh studies into its K-12 curriculum. The Sikh Coalition collaborated with the Alabama Sikh community and education officials to achieve this milestone, aiming to combat bullying and promote inclusivity. A national report highlighted the prevalence of bullying against Sikh students, emphasizing the need for inclusive education.
title: School curriculum in Alabama to include Sikh studies

description: NDP Leader Jagmeet Singh announced his intention to vote against PM Justin Trudeau's Liberal government in an upcoming no-confidence motion.  Singh criticised Trudeau's leadership, citing broken promises and a failure to prioritize the needs of Canadians.  The motion could trigger an election when Parliament resumes on January 27, 2025.  Meanwhile, Trudeau is reportedly planning a cabinet reshuffle.
title: Trudeau on way out? Key ally says will vote to bring him down

description: Former Indian coach Ravi Shastri believes India's gritty final day stand in the Brisbane Test, particularly the last-wicket resistance, has instilled crucial psychological momentum heading into the Boxing Day Test. He compared it to similar rearguard actions, like Bumrah and Shami's partnership at Lord's and the Ashwin-Vihari stand in Sydney, highlighting how such resilience elevates the team's morale.
title: 'It reminded me of ... ': Shastri on India's follow-on celebrations

description: BJP members and Hindu organizations protested in Coimbatore against the state government's handling of the funeral of S.A. Basha, a convict in the 1998 Coimbatore bombings.  Police detained BJP state president K. Annamalai and other leaders for holding the unauthorized "Black Day" procession.  Annamalai criticized the government for allegedly glorifying a terrorist responsible for 58 deaths.
title: TN: Police detains BJP's Annamalai amid protests over blast convict's funeral

description: The US government teeters on the edge of a shutdown as Republicans, influenced by Trump and Musk, rejected a bipartisan funding deal.  Their proposed three-month extension also failed, threatening a partial shutdown on Saturday.  Millions of federal workers face furloughs, impacting essential services and the economy, echoing past shutdown crises.
title: US govt shutdown looms: What will be the impact and has it happened before?
How Rahul, Priyanka hogged limelight during Parliament session

description: Bollywood buzzed with star-studded events! Abhishek and Aishwarya Rai Bachchan united for Aaradhya's school performance, dispelling divorce rumors.  Virat Kohli defended his children's privacy from paparazzi.  Kareena Kapoor and Shahid Kapoor's reunion at their kids' school sparked Jab We Met nostalgia.  Sonu Sood reminisced about Aishwarya comparing him to Amitabh Bachchan. Govind Namdev clarified dating rumors.
title: Top 5 entertainment news

description: Tech leaders, once opposed to Donald Trump, are now flocking to Mar-a-Lago for private dinners.  Zuckerberg, Brin, Bezos, and Musk have all met with the president-elect, seeking influence and aiming to protect their companies from potential political backlash. This marks a significant shift from the 2016 election, when many kept their distance.
title: ‘Everybody wants to be my friend’: Trump marvels at tech titan attention

description: Elon Musk endorsed Germany's far-right AfD party, calling them the country's savior ahead of the February 23rd election.  The AfD, currently second in polls, has been labeled a suspected extremist group.  Mainstream parties refuse to collaborate with them. Musk's endorsement followed criticism of the leading conservative candidate by a right-wing influencer.  AfD leaders celebrated Musk's support.
title: Elon Musk now says only 'extremist' AfD party can save Germany

description: Virat Kohli's new haircut has created buzz ahead of the Boxing Day Test, as India seeks to level the Border-Gavaskar Trophy at 2-1. Following a mixed series performance, Kohli's resurgence is crucial for India's middle order. With the WTC final spot hanging in the balance, India must address top-order inconsistencies and reduce reliance on Bumrah.
title: Watch: Virat Kohli gets a new hairdo ahead of Boxing Day Test

description: YouTube is cracking down on clickbait in India.  The platform will remove videos with misleading titles and thumbnails.  The new rules focus on news and current events.  Creators will have time to adapt to the guidelines.  Enforcement begins with new uploads.  YouTube aims to improve user experience and combat misinformation.
title: YouTube to content creators in India: We will ‘ban’ such videos

description: BJP leader Navya Haridas has filed a petition in the Kerala High Court challenging Priyanka Gandhi Vadra's Wayanad Lok Sabha seat victory.  Haridas alleges that Vadra provided false information about her family's assets in her nomination papers, influencing voters and violating the Model Code of Conduct.  A hearing is expected in January 2025.  Vadra won the seat on November 13th.
title: BJP's Navya Haridas challenges Priyanka's election from Wayanad

description: Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge criticised Prime Minister Modi's handling of the ongoing farmers' protests, citing the farmer leader's hunger strike and unfulfilled promises regarding Minimum Support Price (MSP).  Kharge urged the government to engage in dialogue and address the farmers' concerns, emphasizing their importance to the nation.
title: 'Betraying country': Kharge slams PM Modi over anti-farmer policies

description: The government has increased the Minimum Support Price (MSP) for copra for the 2025 season. Milling copra's MSP is set at Rs 11,582 per quintal, while ball copra's is Rs 12,100. This represents a substantial increase of over 120% since 2014. The hike aims to benefit coconut growers, boost copra production, and meet growing market demands.
title: Centre hikes MSP for Copra by up to 121%

description: A 39-member Joint Parliamentary Committee (JPC), chaired by BJP MP PP Chaudhary, has been formed to review the bills enabling 'One Nation, One Election.' The committee, comprising members from various parties, including prominent BJP and opposition leaders, will analyze the feasibility of simultaneous elections and submit its report by the next parliamentary session's last week.
title: BJP MP PP Chaudhary to head 39-member panel on ONOE

description: President-elect Trump pressed the EU to reduce its trade deficit with the US by buying more American oil and gas, threatening tariffs otherwise. The EU responded with a willingness to discuss strengthening trade relations, particularly in energy, while acknowledging the existing trade imbalance.
title: 'Buy more oil and gas or... ': Trump warns EU over trade deficit

description: Delhi Police Crime Branch will now investigate the Parliament scuffle after complaints from both BJP and Congress.  BJP accused Rahul Gandhi of assault and filed an FIR, citing injuries to two MPs.  Congress countered, alleging BJP MPs pushed Mallikarjun Kharge and manhandled Gandhi.  The incident stemmed from a clash over alleged insults to Dr BR Ambedkar.
title: Parliament scuffle: Crime Branch to probe complaints filed by BJP, Congress

description: India has accused Canada of supporting anti-India separatist agendas through unsubstantiated criminal allegations against Indian citizens.  The Indian government has requested Canada to act against anti-India elements operating within its borders, while also investigating US-shared intelligence regarding organized crime and terrorism linked to Indian nationals.  India assures its citizens abroad that their safety is a top priority.
title: Centre accuses Canada of 'servicing anti-India separatist agenda'

description: India's Parliament was informed that 2,200 cases of violence against minorities were reported in Bangladesh this year until December 8, while Pakistan saw 112 cases until October.  India has expressed concerns to both nations, urging them to ensure the safety and well-being of minorities.  The Indian High Commission in Dhaka is closely monitoring the situation in Bangladesh.
title: '2,200 cases in B'desh, 112 in Pak': Centre highlights violence against Hindus, minorities

description: The high-flying Milwaukee Bucks, fresh off their Emirates NBA Cup victory, face a tough test against the league-leading Cleveland Cavaliers at Rocket Mortgage FieldHouse.  With Damian Lillard out, the Bucks face an uphill battle against a Cavs team that has dominated recent matchups. The game tips off Friday, December 20th at 7:30 PM ET.
title: Bucks vs Cavaliers (12/20): Lineups, start time, prediction, betting tips & more

description: Karnataka BJP MLC CT Ravi, arrested for allegedly using derogatory language against state minister Laxmi Hebbalkar, has been granted bail.  Ravi criticized the Congress government, calling their actions dictatorial and alleging a plot to kill him using a false complaint. He also accused the police of inaction regarding his own complaints.
title: K'taka BJP leader CT Ravi gets bail in 'derogatory' remarks case

description: Cricket legend Sachin Tendulkar shared a video showcasing the impressive bowling action of Sushila Meena, a young talent from rural Rajasthan.  Tendulkar likened her smooth left-arm pace to that of Zaheer Khan, sparking widespread praise and highlighting the untapped potential in India's grassroots cricket.  This recognition could open doors to a brighter future for young talents like Sushila.
title: Watch: Sachin mighty impressed with village girl's bowling

description: A viral video showcasing flashing streetlights at a New York Walmart has sparked online speculation about alien activity and infrastructure tests.  Similar incidents reported across the US, including at a North Carolina airport, fuel these theories.  While some suggest connections to recent drone sightings, others attribute the phenomenon to electrical issues.
title: Lights flashing at night in New York: Aliens, drones…residents wonder at mystery

description: A family in Andhra Pradesh received a parcel containing a decomposing body and an extortion letter demanding Rs 1.36 crore. The letter linked the demand to a loan allegedly taken by the recipient's missing husband.  Suspicion has fallen on the recipient's brother-in-law, who has disappeared. Police are investigating the complex case, suspecting internal family disputes are connected to the crime.
title: Andhra woman expects appliances, gets dead body in parcel instead

description: Chennai Super Kings captain Ruturaj Gaikwad jokingly blamed Royal Challengers Bangalore for a microphone malfunction during an event in Bengaluru.  Gaikwad, retained by CSK for Rs 18 crore, will be next seen leading Maharashtra in the upcoming Vijay Hazare Trophy.
title: 'Bro chose violence': CSK skipper roasts RCB. Watch

description: Ministry of defence signed a Rs 7,629 crore contract with L&T for 100 K-9 Vajra-T self-propelled howitzers, adding to the 100 already in service.  These 155mm guns, with a 28-38 km range, are designed for high-altitude deployment along the China border and boost the Army's firepower amid modernization efforts and lessons from the Ukraine war.
title: Eye on China, India inks Rs 7,629cr deal for 100 K-9 Vajra-T artillery guns

description: A housekeeping employee at a Delhi government hospital was arrested for secretly filming inside the women's washroom. A woman discovered a hidden phone recording, leading to the arrest. The accused confessed to filming for a month. This incident follows a similar case in Bengaluru where a coffee shop employee hid a phone in the restroom dustbin, raising privacy concerns.
title: Man held for secretly filming women in Delhi hospital washroom

description: India's World Test Championship (WTC) Final hopes hang in the balance as the Border-Gavaskar Trophy reaches its climax.  Level at 1-1, any series loss eliminates India from contention.  Sri Lanka could even leapfrog them with a 2-0 victory against Australia. India must secure at least a draw to keep their WTC Final dream alive.
title: What are India's chances for WTC Final if they lose BGT?

description: Indian equity markets suffered a five-day losing streak, shedding ₹18.43 lakh crore in market value.  The Sensex plummeted nearly 5%, driven by foreign fund outflows and global uncertainties.  The US Federal Reserve's hawkish stance further dampened investor sentiment, impacting various sectors like IT, financials, and realty.
title: Investors lose over Rs 18 lakh crore in 5-day market rout

description: US expresses serious concerns over Pakistan's advancing long-range missile program, capable of reaching American soil. Washington imposed sanctions on Pakistan's National Development Complex and private companies, marking a shift in US-Pakistan relations. Islamabad dismisses US concerns, citing the program as defensive and aimed at countering India, while Washington questions Pakistan's intentions and its growing ties with China.
title: Soon, Pak missiles could strike America: What it means for India

description: A family in Andhra Pradesh received a shocking delivery – a dead body in a parcel with a ransom note demanding ₹1.3 crore.  The recipient, Sagi Tulasi, whose husband disappeared ten years ago, had been receiving anonymous gifts. Police suspect family involvement, particularly Tulasi's brother-in-law, who is now missing.
title: Andhra woman receives parcel, finds decomposed body inside

description: Elon Musk advised people to get Starlink as a backup internet.  Morgan Housel praised Starlink after using it during an internet outage.  Former Intel CEO Pat Gelsinger supported Musk's advice.  He highlighted the importance of a secondary internet connection.  Starlink can provide reliable internet access during emergencies.  It offers high speed and low latency.
title: I love ...: Fired Intel CEO Pat Gelsinger on Elon Musk’s Starlink post

description: The ICC confirmed a hybrid model for the 2025 Champions Trophy, with India's matches at a neutral venue due to security concerns in Pakistan.  Out-of-favour Ahmad Shahzad's recently made a sarcastic suggestion of a border stadium for India-Pakistan matches highlighting the complexities. Shahzad believes Pakistan lost a golden opportunity to host India, dimming future prospects.
title: 'Border pe stadium, ek gate India ki side': Shahzad's bizarre solution

description: The Telangana High Court has granted interim protection from arrest to BRS MLA KT Rama Rao until December 30 in the Formula E race case. The ACB had filed a case against Rama Rao, alleging unauthorized payments and foreign currency transactions related to organizing the race. The case is scheduled for further hearing on December 27.
title: Formula E case: KTR Rao gets protection from arrest till Dec 30

description: A Bengaluru techie's mother has filed a habeas corpus plea in the Supreme Court seeking custody of her four-year-old grandson after her son's suicide. The techie had accused his wife and in-laws of harassment in a suicide note and video. The Supreme Court has issued a notice to Haryana, Karnataka, and Uttar Pradesh governments, with a hearing scheduled for January 7, 2025. The child's whereabouts are currently unknown.
title: Atul Subhash's mother moves SC for grandson's custody

description: A horrific accident occurred on the Jaipur-Ajmer highway. A chemical truck and LPG tanker collided.  A massive fire erupted.  Several vehicles, including a bus, caught fire.  Nine people died.  Over 40 people suffered injuries.  Survivors escaped through bus windows.  Many injured have severe burns.  Officials are providing medical assistance.
title: 'Broke window, jumped out': Survivor recounts horrific Jaipur blaze

description: India has expressed serious concern to the US government regarding threats made by Sikh separatist Gurpatwant Singh Pannun against Indian Ambassador Vinay Kwatra. Pannun, designated a terrorist, accused Kwatra of coordinating with Russian agencies against pro-Khalistan Sikhs. India expects the US to address these security concerns.
title: 'Expect US to take it seriously': India flags threats to envoy from K-terrorist
How Parliament descended into protests, brawls and chaos

description: India lodged a strong protest with Bangladesh over a Facebook post by Mahfuz Alam, an adviser to the interim government, suggesting annexation of Indian territories. Alam's post, made on Bangladesh's Victory Day, accused India of containing Bangladesh's growth and linked past events to efforts to reduce Bangladesh's dependence on India. The post has since been deleted.
title: 'Be mindful': India raps B'desh over now-deleted 'annex' post by key aide

description: Bulgarian mystic Baba Vanga's predictions for 2025 range from unsettling to hopeful. A European war, alien contact, and telepathy development are foreseen, alongside lab-grown organs, a new energy source, and Lewis Hamilton's 8th championship win. Increased natural disasters, a new world system, medical breakthroughs, global tensions, a new currency, and a space exploration era are also predicted. Some of her forecasts have been contested, but others have extraordinarily materialized.
title: Take a look at Baba Vanga's mysterious predictions for 2025

description: Popular leadership expert Robin Sharma emphasizes prioritizing energy management over intellect for achieving true success and well-being.  He advocates for practices like morning exercise, healthy eating, nature walks, and quality sleep, alongside disengaging from negativity to protect one's energy and cultivate inner peace. Sharma believes integrity and kindness, though sometimes perceived as weaknesses, ultimately lead to a fulfilling life.
title: Robin Sharma on why protecting one's energy is more important than intelligence

description: Samsung is offering attractive holiday deals on its flagship smartphones. The Galaxy Z Fold6 and Z Flip6 are available with substantial discounts and 24-month no-cost EMI options. Significant price drops also apply to the Galaxy S24 Ultra, S24, S24+, S24 FE, S23 Ultra, S23, and S23 FE, with various cashback and EMI offers.
title: Samsung announces Holiday Sale on phones and smartwatches

description: Indian student enrollment in the UK has surged by 273.9% from 2019 to 2023, driven by the country’s top-ranked universities and the Graduate Route Visa. This visa allows students to stay up to three years post-study, offering work opportunities and family relocation. Additionally, the India-UK Mutual Recognition of Qualifications fosters academic and career growth, further boosting UK appeal.
title: Indian student enrollment in UK up 273.9% since 2019: Is graduate route visa the key?

description: Australia's selectors have drafted uncapped teenager Sam Konstas into the squad for the crucial Boxing Day Test against India. Seeking a more dynamic approach against India's potent pace attack, selectors aim to shake up their struggling top order. Konstas' unique batting style offers a potential solution to the slow scoring rates of Khawaja, McSweeney, and Labuschagne.
title: 'To throw something different at India': Aus selector defends squad changes

description: Samajwadi Party MP Jaya Bachchan accused BJP MPs of feigning injuries during a parliamentary clash, suggesting their dramatic falls deserved acting awards. The confrontation stemmed from INDIA bloc protests against alleged disrespect towards Dr. B.R. Ambedkar. Bachchan questioned the BJP's narrative, while Rahul Gandhi denied allegations of pushing and misbehavior.
title: 'Deserve Oscars': Jaya Bachchan accuses BJP MPs of faking injuries

description: Karnataka BJP MLC CT Ravi, arrested for derogatory remarks against a minister, accused the Congress government of acting like dictators.  He alleged a conspiracy to kill him through a false case.  Fellow BJP leader HD Kumaraswamy condemned the attack on Ravi and questioned the state's democratic values and police conduct.
title: 'Acting like dictators': BJP's CT Ravi slams K'taka govt after arrest

description: Sambhal MP Zia Ur Rehman's house steps were demolished in an "anti-encroachment" drive.  He was also fined ₹1.91 crore for alleged electricity theft and his power supply disconnected.  Rehman faces charges related to November's mosque survey violence. His father, Mamlukur Rehman Barq, was booked for threatening officials during the electricity inspection.
title: Steps leading to Sambhal MP Zia Ur Rehman's home bulldozed

description: Nineteen-year-old Isabella Strahan, daughter of NFL legend Michael Strahan, triumphed over cancer and embarked on a modeling career.  Five months post-chemotherapy, she graced the cover of Town & Country and appeared for The Woman 360.  Her journey, documented on YouTube, showcases her resilience and family support as she balances modeling with studies at USC.
title: Michael Strahan’s daughter makes inspiring career move after her battle with cancer
‘Cold as ice’ and smirking: Mangione’s perp walk body language decoded

description: Chess grandmaster Magnus Carlsen stirred the pot by declaring faster chess formats the "pure sport", criticising classical chess for being "too forgiving". He argued that rapid and blitz chess better reflect a player's all-around skills. Carlsen also critiqued the recent World Championship match between Gukesh and Ding, deeming the quality subpar.
title: 'Classical chess probably the worst': Carlsen after Gukesh crowned champion

description: Tragedy struck off Rhodes as a migrant speedboat capsized during an attempted evasion of Greek authorities, leaving eight dead and 18 rescued. A frantic search continues for potentially missing passengers. This incident follows another deadly sinking south of Crete last weekend, claiming seven lives.
title: 8 dead as boat carrying migrants sinks off Greek island

description: Infosys inaugurated a ₹426 crore development center in West Bengal, creating 4,000 IT jobs.  Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee celebrated this as a boost to the state's IT sector, alongside the development of a 200-acre "Silicon Valley" projected to generate 75,000 more jobs.
title: Infosys' "New Year gift" to Bengal CM, here's what Mamata Banerjee said

description: 'Pushpa 2' will cross Rs 1000 crore at the box office in India, in all languages by the end of Friday. The film can be expected to see a good jump over the coming weekend which will be its third Saturday and Sunday.
title: The Allu Arjun starrer Pushpa 2 set to cross Rs 1000 crore net today

description: Breon Peace, the US Attorney who brought charges against industrialist Gautam Adani, is resigning on January 10, 2025, weeks before Trump's inauguration. His tenure included high-profile cases like the R. Kelly trial. Peace expressed gratitude for his team's work in upholding the rule of law and promoting civil rights. Carolyn Pokorny will become Acting US Attorney.
title: US attorney Breon Peace who indicted Gautam Adani resigns

description: Former Australian skipper Michael Clarke has slammed the national selectors for dropping opener Nathan McSweeney mid-series against India. Clarke argued that the selectors should have given McSweeney the entire series, regardless of his lean patch. He questioned the decision, especially considering the struggles of senior players like Khawaja and Labuschagne.
title: 'Got this wrong': Ex-Australia skipper blasts selectors over BGT squad

description: Rajya Sabha Chairman Jagdeep Dhankhar criticized parliamentarians for frequent disruptions during the winter session, which concluded with only 40% productivity.  He urged members to engage in meaningful debates instead of destructive behavior, emphasizing the need to restore public trust in democratic institutions.  The session saw the formation of a joint parliamentary committee on simultaneous elections amidst continued opposition protests.
title: 'World watches us, yet we fail our citizens': VP on Parliament disruptions
Police on alert after unclaimed bag found near Delhi BJP office; probe on

description: A gas tanker collided with vehicles on the Jaipur-Ajmer highway.  The collision caused a large fire.  Nine people died.  Fifteen people suffered critical burns.  Forty-three people are in hospital.  The fire affected a 300-meter stretch of highway.  A search and rescue operation is underway.
title: CCTV captures deadly gas tanker crash on Jaipur-Ajmer highway: 9 dead, 15 critical

description: Philadelphia Eagles running back Saquon Barkley's MVP candidacy hinges on breaking Eric Dickerson's single-season rushing record, according to former teammate Jason Kelce. Barkley's remarkable 1688-yard season needs a final push to surpass Dickerson's 2105 yards. While leading the league in rushing, Barkley faces stiff competition from quarterbacks Josh Allen and Lamar Jackson.
title: Can Saquon Barkley win NFL MVP? Jason Kelce pinpoints one thing he must do

description: Indian cinema is witnessing a box office boom, with films increasingly crossing the Rs 1,000 crore mark.  Trade analysts attribute this success to strategic release planning, pan-Indian appeal, aggressive marketing, and the rise of franchises. While the milestone remains exclusive, it signifies a shift in audience preferences and the evolving landscape of Indian filmmaking.
title: Pushpa 2, Jawan, KGF: Is Rs 1000 crore the new benchmark for success?

description: Nidhhi Agerwal is at a crucial moment in her career, starring as the female lead in two major projects: 'Hari Hara Veera Mallu' with Pawan Kalyan and 'Raja Saab' with Prabhas. A leaked photo from Raja Saab went viral, but she clarified it was from an ad shoot, generating publicity.
title: Nidhhi Agerwal's LEAKED pic sparks buzz; actress confirms it's not from set

description: A mysterious illness called "Dinga Dinga," causing shaking, fever, and weakness, is affecting women and girls in Uganda's Bundibugyo district. This mysterious illness serves as a stark reminder of the importance of vigilance in detecting and managing emerging diseases. The cause is unknown, but investigations are underway, with samples sent to the Ministry of Health for analysis.
title: Dinga Dinga virus: Why women are dancing uncontrollably in this infection

description: WhatsApp has launched three limited-time features for Android and iPhone users to celebrate the New Year.  These include festive video call effects, animated reactions for celebratory emojis, and curated New Year's Eve sticker packs. The features are available from December 20th through January 3rd. Users can access them by updating to the latest version of WhatsApp.
title: You have only 15 days to use these 'special' WhatsApp features

description: The National Testing Agency (NTA) has released the schedule for the UGC NET December 2024 exam, which will take place from January 3 to January 16, 2025. The exam will be conducted in two shifts and cover various subjects. Candidates can access the detailed schedule on the official website. It is crucial to follow the steps provided for downloading the timetable and ensure timely preparation for the exams.
title: UGC NET December 2024 exam schedule released: Check timetable here

description: Prithvi Shaw's exclusion from the Vijay Hazare Trophy squad sparked controversy after the Mumbai Cricket Association (MCA) cited disciplinary issues and poor fitness as reasons. An MCA official revealed that Shaw's on-field performance was hampered by his fitness, and his attitude has drawn complaints from teammates. Shaw's frequent late-night partying and disregard for training regimens further fueled the MCA's decision.
title: 'Prithvi Shaw is his own enemy': MCA slams batter's outburst

description: ITR filing deadline: December 31, 2024, is the last chance to file belated or revised income tax returns for FY 2023-24.  Missing this deadline means penalties, loss of refunds and certain claims.
title: ITR filing: Don’t miss Dec 31 deadline for revised, belated tax returns
Parliament winter session comes to end amid BJP-INDIA bloc showdown

description: Ravichandran Ashwin, one of India's finest spinners, retired from international cricket after a 14-year career. He finished with 537 Test wickets, second only to Anil Kumble in Indian cricket history. While Kumble holds the record for most wickets, Ashwin achieved milestones faster and boasts superior bowling averages and strike rates.
title: R Ashwin vs Anil Kumble: A tale of India's two spin legends

description: The CAT 2024 results highlight a continued dominance of engineers, with 13 out of 14 candidates achieving a perfect 100 percentile. Engineers made up 86% of the top 73 scorers, a rise from 73% in 2023. This growing disparity raises concerns about the representation of non-engineers in top management institutes, highlighting a systemic advantage for engineers in the exam.
title: Engineers dominate CAT 2024 results with 13 achieving perfect 100 percentiles

description: Former Pakistani cricketer Rashid Latif believes the ICC's decision to hold India-Pakistan matches at neutral venues until 2027 should have been implemented after the 2017 Champions Trophy. While acknowledging India's influence in the decision, he stresses the financial implications for both nations.
title: CT: How ICC's planning 'will benefit both India and Pakistan'

description: India strengthens KYC data security by masking sensitive identifiers like Aadhaar and PAN. The deadline for this change, initially December 2024, is now extended to January 20, 2025, giving institutions and individuals more time to adapt.
title: This KYC deadline for Aadhaar, PAN & more extended to January 20

description: Harbhajan Singh shared how his feud with Andrew Symonds transformed into a deep friendship after the infamous "Monkeygate" scandal.  Symonds' visit to Harbhajan's home with a bottle of rum initiated their reconciliation. They later won the IPL championship together. Harbhajan expressed grief over Symonds' untimely death, highlighting their strong bond.
title: 'A long hug': Harbhajan on how feud turned to friendship with Symonds

description: Priyanka Gandhi Vadra criticized Amit Shah's remarks on Ambedkar, deeming them insulting and intolerable. She defended Rahul Gandhi against accusations of pushing a BJP MP during a parliamentary scuffle, calling the claims baseless. The Congress leader also accused the government of fearing discussion on the Adani controversy and stifling opposition unity.
title: 'Rahul can never push anyone,' Priyanka slams BJP's allegations of violence

description: Former Haryana chief minister and INLD chief Om Prakash Chautala passed away at 89 after suffering a cardiac arrest at his Gurgaon residence.  Chautala, a five-time chief minister, was rushed to Medanta Hospital but couldn't be saved. Haryana CM Manohar Lal Khattar and other political leaders expressed condolences, remembering Chautala's service to the state and society.
title: Former Haryana CM and INLD leader OP Chautala passes away at 89

description: A Delhi de-addiction center was uncovered as a front for drug peddling, supplying high doses of narcotics to patients and youth.  Fake doctors prescribed dangerous drug combinations, worsening addictions. Police raided the center, seizing drugs and records, and are pursuing the absconded owner.
title: 'Deaddiction’ centre was a ‘readdiction’ centre', fake docs prescribed drugs in high doses

description: A Navy speedboat collision with an Elephanta Island ferry near Mumbai raised the death toll to 14, with one child still missing. The overloaded ferry carried over 100 passengers.  Authorities are investigating the crash, focusing on the speedboat's recent engine replacement and testing.  New life jacket rules are now being enforced for ferries.
title: Mumbai boat crash: Operators question Navy's reluctance to halt vessel tests

description: Five asteroids are approaching Earth in the coming days, with the largest, the airplane-sized 2024 XN1, passing by on December 24th at a safe distance of over 4.4 million miles.  Several smaller asteroids will also make closer passes before then, all monitored by NASA's Asteroid Watch. None of the asteroids pose a threat to Earth.
title: Nasa on alert as 120-foot asteroid to approach Earth on Christmas eve

description: Indian cricket captain Rohit Sharma's forgetful moments have become endearing to fans.  A recent anecdote shared by Pakistan's Imam-ul-Haq recounts how Rohit left his phone on a plane during the 2023 World Cup, and Babar Azam returned it. This incident highlights Rohit's laid-back personality, adding to his charm and relatability.
title: Watch: Imam-ul-Haq hilariously recalls Rohit Sharma's forgetful incidents

description: President Putin has publicly accused Google and YouTube of political manipulation and intentional service degradation in Russia. He claims Google is a US government tool and YouTube's slow speeds are due to inadequate infrastructure investment, a claim Google denies. While Russia hasn't blocked YouTube, Putin emphasized the growth of Russian alternatives.

title: White House emergency? Biden, Harris 'cancel Christmas trips and rush back'

description: Cricket Australia's National Cricket Centre in Brisbane is a key factor in Australia's cricket success. The facility boasts advanced training and recovery resources. It includes multiple playing surfaces mimicking conditions worldwide. The NCC supports various cricket teams and programs. Even during a busy schedule, the center remains active with training and other activities.
title: Inside Australia's National Cricket Centre: Where champions are made

description: The Supreme Court upheld the Allahabad High Court's decision, making the DND Flyway toll-free for commuters between Delhi and Noida. This ruling follows a 2016 CAG audit and a resident welfare association's petition citing excessive tolls despite persistent road maintenance issues. The Noida Toll Bridge Company, claiming financial strain, maintains the flyway despite the halted toll collection.
title: DND flyway to remain toll-free; SC dismisses appeal against HC order
Drone flight ban imposed in New York, New Jersey: What you need to know

description: BJP MP Aprajita Sarangi gave Congress leader Priyanka Gandhi Vadra a bag with '1984' printed on it, referencing the anti-Sikh riots. This followed a Parliament clash over Ambedkar, resulting in injuries to two BJP MPs. Priyanka Gandhi's support for Palestine and Bangladeshi minorities, displayed through bags, drew BJP criticism, with accusations of "appeasement" and comparisons to the "New Muslim League".
title: Watch: BJP gifts a tote bag to Priyanka Gandhi with '1984' printed on it

description: Samajwadi Party MP Zia Ur Rehman Barq faces a ₹1.91 crore fine for alleged electricity theft at his Sambhal residence. A power department raid, following a police case, revealed tampered meters and zero consumption recorded despite heavy appliance usage. The sanctioned load of 2KW was drastically exceeded by the actual usage of 16,480 watts.
title: Sambhal violence accused SP MP slapped with Rs 1.9cr fine for 'electricity theft'

description: Ravichandran Ashwin announced his retirement from international cricket after the drawn third Test against Australia.  Cricket legends Sachin Tendulkar and Kapil Dev personally congratulated Ashwin, who shared a screenshot of his call log.  Ashwin finished his career as India's second-highest Test wicket-taker and a key figure in their home Test dominance.
title: Who called R Ashwin after retirement? Cricketer shares call log pic

description: Elon Musk's influence on the Republican Party and the Trump administration is raising concerns. His criticism of a bipartisan budget deal led to its failure, prompting some Republicans to suggest him as House speaker. Democrats expressed alarm at his power, while some Republicans voiced frustration over his intervention's impact on farmers.
title: Why Democrats have started referring to Tesla CEO as 'President Musk'

description: Former India coach Ravi Shastri lauded Ravichandran Ashwin's relentless pursuit of excellence following the all-rounder's retirement.  Shastri highlighted Ashwin's constant innovation, 765 international wickets, and exceptional recent form,  emphasizing his status as a match-winner. He also praised the synergistic partnership between Ashwin and Jadeja,  noting their complementary roles in each other's success.
title: Ravi Shastri reveals the secret behind R Ashwin's greatness

description: Google has streamlined its management structure, cutting 10% of manager, director, and VP roles over two years.  This restructuring, part of a broader efficiency drive, mirrors Amazon's approach and aims to accelerate decision-making in the face of rising AI competition.  CEO Sundar Pichai also signaled a shift in Google's corporate culture.
title: Google CEO updates on job cuts in town hall: 10% management roles cut

description: Income Tax authorities unearthed 52kg of gold and Rs 10 crore cash from an abandoned vehicle near Bhopal, linked to raids on real estate firms. The operation, targeting 52 locations across three districts, focuses on Trishul Construction and its owner, Rajesh Sharma, along with associated individuals and companies.
title: IT raids: 52 kg gold, over Rs 10cr cash found in abandoned vehicle

description: Melania Trump has maintained a noticeably lower profile during Donald Trump's second presidential campaign, sparking speculation about their relationship. Despite limited public appearances alongside her husband, a recent photo of the couple kissing at a baseball game has circulated widely.
title: Trump & Melania's kiss at basketball game goes viral: 'Let the woman breathe'

description: A bizarre run-out unfolded during the West Indies vs. Bangladesh T20I. Jaker Ali, initially given out, was called back from the dressing room after replays revealed his partner, Shamim Hossain, was short of his crease. Shamim's bat was airborne as Jaker slid his bat in, leading to a comical mix-up. The umpires overturned the decision, sending Shamim back instead.
title: Watch: Batter called back from dressing room after run out fiasco
Why was Stonehenge built? Scientists finally solve 5,000-year-old mystery

description: Amazon is delaying its mandatory five-day office return for some corporate employees until as late as May 2025 due to insufficient workspace in several US cities.  This contradicts earlier guidance and impacts an unknown number of its 350,000 corporate staff.  The delay follows employee pushback against the policy and existing challenges with the current hybrid model.
title: Amazon is now telling employees to not to return to office, the reason is...

description: Ravichandran Ashwin announced his retirement from international cricket after the Brisbane Test against Australia.  The 38-year-old's unexpected decision prompted tributes from teammates like Virat Kohli and Ravi Shastri, along with celebrities and fans.  Ashwin responded with a mix of gratitude and humor on social media, marking the end of his illustrious cricketing career.
title: Ashwin makes witty response to Virat Kohli's emotional farewell post

description: India's government grapples with a massive rice surplus, exceeding four times the required stock.  Despite offering a large quantity for ethanol production, there are no takers.  To address this, the government considers lowering the sale price for distilleries and potentially allowing sugar exports to manage the excess stock.
title: Stuck with excess rice stock, govt may cut rate for ethanol makers

description: Travis Kelce surprised Taylor Swift with an Eras Tour-themed birthday party, complete with props and a recreation of the iconic "22" hat moment.  The celebration marked the end of Swift's record-breaking tour, attended by close friends and family.  Even Brittany and Patrick Mahomes joined the festivities, embracing the tour's spirit with themed attire.
title: Travis Kelce throws wrap party, surprises Taylor Swift with '22 Hat' gift

description: Putin expressed readiness to discuss Ukraine with Trump, highlighting a potential shift in US-Russia relations.  He also boasted about Russia's "Oreshnik" hypersonic missile and challenged Western defense systems with a provocative test-launch proposal targeting Kyiv.  Putin congratulated Trump on his election victory, expressing optimism for future US-Russia relations.
title: 'Ready to meet any time': Putin open to talks with Trump on Ukraine

description: Pakistan beat South Africa by 81 runs in the second ODI. They clinched the series 2-0. Babar Azam and Mohammad Rizwan scored 73 and 80 runs respectively. Shaheen Afridi and Naseem Shah took key wickets. A heated exchange occurred between players. Heinrich Klaasen argued with Haris Rauf and Rizwan. Babar Azam intervened to calm things down.
title: Watch: Rizwan's verbal clash with Klaasen, Babar acts as pacifier

description: A fiery truck collision involving a chemical-laden truck disrupted the Jaipur-Ajmer highway on Friday morning. Several trucks caught fire near a petrol pump, causing burn injuries to an unspecified number of people. Ambulances transported the injured to hospitals while firefighters battled the blaze. Traffic on the highway came to a standstill as authorities worked to control the situation.
title: 4 dead after truck carrying chemicals catches fire after mishap near fuel pump

description: India defeated West Indies by 60 runs in Navi Mumbai to clinch the T20I series 2-1, their first home series victory in five years.  Smriti Mandhana led with a 47-ball 77, while Richa Ghosh's 21-ball 54 propelled India to a record 217/4.  West Indies' bowling faltered, allowing India to capitalize and secure a comfortable win.
title: How Smriti's pep talk inspired India to first home series win since 2019

description: The Denver Broncos face the Los Angeles Chargers in a crucial Week 16 matchup with significant playoff implications. A win or tie secures the Broncos a wild-card spot, their first since 2015. A loss, however, complicates their path, requiring other games to fall in their favor. The Chargers, with a high playoff probability, have multiple scenarios to clinch this week.
title: Broncos’ chances to the 2024 NFL playoffs: What’s at stake as Denver faces Chargers

description: India and Australia face selection dilemmas for the fourth Test, grappling with underperforming batting lineups.  Australia's top order woes contrast with India's middle-order struggles. Both captains emphasize team attitude amidst calls for change, with younger players likely to get more opportunities while veterans face pressure to perform.
title: Boxing Day Test: Batting order questions for India, Australia

description: Luigi Mangione, accused of murdering UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson, is held at Brooklyn's Metropolitan Detention Center (MDC), alongside rapper Sean "Diddy" Combs.  Both share the same lawyer, Marc Agnifilo.  Mangione faces federal murder charges, potentially including the death penalty, and awaits trial in the notorious MDC, known for its harsh conditions and high-profile inmates.

description: Nuvama recommends holding Ambuja Cements, anticipating growth after its merger with Shanghi Industries and Penna Cement. description: The White House has voiced serious concerns over Pakistan's advancing missile program, calling it an emerging threat to the US.  New sanctions target Pakistani entities, including a state-owned enterprise, for contributing to long-range ballistic missile development.  Officials warn Pakistan could soon possess missiles capable of reaching beyond South Asia, questioning Islamabad's intentions despite US support and diplomatic efforts.

description: Former Karnataka minister CT Ravi, arrested for derogatory remarks against minister Laxmi Hebbalkar, alleges a murder conspiracy and police negligence.  He claims a false case was filed and holds the Congress government responsible if anything happens to him.  The BJP leader was detained following a heated argument between parties, sparking accusations and denials from both sides.

description: Pushpa 2's box office collection declined on day 15.  The film earned Rs 17.75 crore.  The Hindi version led with Rs 14 crore.  The total collection stands at Rs 621.6 crore.  Competition from new releases like Mufasa and Baby John impacted its earnings.  The film's lifetime expectation has been revised to Rs 750 crore.
title: Pushpa 2 box office collection day 15: Film misses Rs 1,000cr mark

description: A clash erupted at the new Parliament building in New Delhi between BJP and Congress MPs over allegations of insulting Ambedkar. BJP MP Pratap Sarangi sustained a head injury during the confrontation and was taken to the hospital, along with colleague Mukesh Rajput. They accused Rahul Gandhi of shoving them, while both parties lodged complaints against each other.
title: Parliament scuffle: No one’s admitting guilt; parties blame each other

description: Nvidia's stock, despite a recent uptick, remains below its peak, slipping to the third most valuable company. Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella's comment on ample chip supply suggests an overinvestment during the AI boom, potentially impacting Nvidia's chip demand.

description: RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat criticized the rise of disputes over religious sites, emphasizing the importance of interfaith harmony in India.  He stated that raising issues out of hate is unacceptable, referencing the Ram temple as a matter of faith. Bhagwat urged a return to ancient culture, rejecting extremism and advocating for inclusivity, where everyone can practice their faith freely.
title: Don't rake up Ram temple-like issues elsewhere: RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat

description: The Supreme Court questioned the Bengal government and its SSC over a teacher recruitment 'scam,' highlighting flaws in the selection process. The court examined various categories of irregularities, including manipulated ranks and marks. While acknowledging the impact on students, the court prioritized addressing the 'scam' confirmed by a commission and the CBI.
title: 'Dal mein kuch kala h ya sab kala h?': SC quizzes Bengal in teacher recruitment 'scam'

description: TCS plans to boost hiring of fresh engineering graduates in FY26, exceeding the current year's target of 40,000.  Driven by optimistic growth projections, the IT giant is also focusing on recruiting experienced professionals for specific, high-growth verticals.  They are investing in training students before graduation and leveraging AI to enhance HR processes, from recruitment to employee support.
title: TCS HR head Milind Lakkad on hiring plans for 2025

description: A 65-year-old Ahmedabad man was defrauded of Rs 1.29 crore by a woman he befriended on Facebook. Posing as a London resident, she and accomplices, including one impersonating a Delhi airport officer, extorted money from him between March and June by threatening legal action over undeclared currency.  The retiree ultimately contacted authorities after realizing the scam.
title: Click, chat, cheat: Online friendship costs Ahmedabad man Rs 1.3 crore
